'''Madarchod''' is a swear word in [[Hindi]] and [[Urdu]]. It is considered to be a strongly vulgar and insulting word, not to be used in everyday conversation.  The term is a natural combination of the words ''''Madar'''' (mother) and ''''Chod'''' (fucker), resulting in a literal translation of 'mother fucker.' It is considered to be the choicest of vulgar incestual insults alongside other variations including '''Bhenchod''', meaning 'sister fucker'.  Usage is popular in India and Pakistan.
